    </div>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">K Management Strategy</h2>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hold for premium squares:</span> K on DLS = 10 points, on TLS = 15. With only one K in the game, it's worth waiting 1-2 turns for a premium square rather than dumping it on a regular tile.</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-CK endings are your friend:</span> KNACK, KNOCK, BRICK, STUCK — the CK pattern appears in hundreds of words. If C is on the board, hook K onto it for instant plays.</p></div>
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KN- silent K openers:</span> KNACK, KNIFE, KNEEL, KNOT — players forget these because the K is silent in speech. In Scrabble, that silent K is worth 5 free points.</p></div>
