      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KALE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">INK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OAK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20"><p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p><p class="text-base text-gray-200">Since there's only <span class="text-white font-medium">1 K in the entire game</span>, once it's played you can stop thinking about K-words entirely. Track it — if it's on the board, free up mental space for other letters.</p></div>
